        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Gate repair lane and tune concurrency",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a default-off repair lane feature flag with workflow and CLI no-op behavior unless CLAWSWEEPER_FEATURE_REPAIR_ENABLED=1\n- keep read-only repair planning, scanning, dry-run requeue, and reporting paths usable when the flag is unset; only live repair dispatch/mutation is opt-in\n- move repair/automerge/issue implementation capacity to explicit automation limits capped at one live run by default\n- prefer existing gitcrawl-store SQLite state before the legacy gitcrawl DB and document that freshness is maintained by the store refresh workflow plus git pull\n- document migrated repair features and add regression coverage for limits, workflow env wiring, unset/set repair dispatch routing, and gitcrawl-store defaults\n\n## Rollout note\n- Maintainer policy for this PR is default-off because ClawSweeper is used across many repositories.\n- Repositories that should keep live repair/autofix/automerge/issue-implementation dispatch must set `CLAWSWEEPER_FEATURE_REPAIR_ENABLED=1`; otherwise ClawSweeper continues read-only review/scan/report behavior without starting executing repair workers.\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm run check\n",
